<title>USA: Hardinge stock jumps; sets buyback of 10 pct of shares.</title>
<headline>Hardinge stock jumps; sets buyback of 10 pct of shares.</headline>
<dateline>ELMIRA, N.Y.</dateline>
<text>
<p>The stock of Hardinge Inc., a maker of machine tools, gained Tuesday after it said its board authorised the buyback of up to 640,000 shares, or about 10 percent of the shares outstanding.</p>
<p>Hardinge was up $1.50 to $23.75 in early trading on the Nasdaq market.</p>
<p>The company said it would buy back the shares through open market transactions from time to time as market conditions warrant.</p>
<p>It said it has 6.47 million shares outstanding.</p>
